          "Course-Halfway Point",
          "Authors aggregate the different types of features at their disposal into one of 6 categories.\n\nAll data is collectec up to week 8, which represents the course’s halfway point. \n\nMoreover, the authors attempt different feature sets. ",
          "TrialExamPure (OneR),\nSingle-Feature LogisticREgression,\n2-Feature Logistic Regression,\nLASSO,\nLogistic Regression with features selected from LASSO,\nXGBoost, Random Forest, SVM, \nXGBoostLasso, RFLasso, SVMLasso\n",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{Accuracy: 0.55 - 2Feature Logistic, Precision_High: 0.94 - 1Feature Logistic, Precision_Medium: 0.39 - 2Feature Logistic, Precision_Low: 0.72 - 2Feature Logistic, Recall_High: 0.59 - OneR, Recall_Medium: 1.00 - SVM & SVMLASSO, Recall_\nLow: 0.99 - RF}",
          "Authors make a comparison of different feature sets. In addition, two distinct approaches are attempted - Classification and Regression.\n\nResults show that there is value in using MSLQ as it does seem that high values on elaboration are predictors of high marks.\n\nSurprisingly, a simple Lasso Regression is capable of outperforming algorithms that are argued to be more powerful.  ",
          "Small sample size, witht he test data belonging to a context that substantially different than the one used for the training data (Covid vs post-Covid).\n\nTeacher behavior and influence can have an effect on the behavior and grades of their students.\n\nNo capture of offline learning activities."
